AUDIO: 'got our first look at one and it\'s free and open [music] source. LTX just dropped LTX desktop, a full local non-linear editor powered by LTX [music] 2.3 and more if you want. So, today'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we\'re going to go through the whole thing. How to install it, [music] what it can do, what it can\'t do, and why it\'s a big deal. On that note, sharpen your razors and sweep the floor. Kicking off with a quick speed run on'

[00:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the model side as LTX 2.3 was also released alongside LTX desktop. And you know, this is a pretty solid update. For one, they rebuilt the VAE. That\'s the part of the architecture that handles'

[00:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the actual image quality. So, you know, sharper details, better textures, cleaner edges. Image to video also got a number of fixes. They reworked the training data on that. So, you should be getting better movement and motion now'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and less chance of things just kind of going static or inert. We also got native portrait video. So, 1080 by 1920 trained on vertical data, not cropped from landscape. And overall audio quality improvements. They cleaned up'

[01:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the training set for silence gaps and noise artifacts. We have tighter sync and a new vocoder. 2.3 is of course available over on Hugging Face and ComfyUI support was there day one. As a quick side note, if you\'ve ever been'

