[01:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pretty interesting. I\'ll definitely take a look at that. And finally, back to LTX 2.3. If you don\'t want to deal with any of the hardware stuff, you can just run it via an API. Uh links will be down below. But honestly, LTX 2.3 is not the big story here. The big story is LTX'

[02:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'desktop. LTX desktop is an open-source fully local non-linear video editor built on the LTX 2.3 engine. Again, just to stress, this is not a web app. This runs locally on your PC, Mac, or well,'

[02:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'no love for Linux, sorry, Linux weirdos. They\'re working on it. And I do say weirdos with the utmost respect and love. Now, some things to go over, both good news and what I hesitate to call it'

