AUDIO: 'etc., um it could get as high as 150 gigs. Mine was about 70 gigs. So, just as an FYI, maybe it\'s time to finally clean out that download folder. I mean, we all need to do that. One thing I do'

[03:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'want to note, at least on the PC side, is that some folks, including myself, actually, had an issue with the installer, uh namely in that it kept failing out. The The solution is uh just right-click on it and then run it as'

[03:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'administrator, and that seems to take care of everything. So, once you do that, um then, you know, go grab a cup of coffee or three, depending on your internet speed. Now, once everything\'s up, you can save some space. For example, with the text encoder, uh the'

[03:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'text encoder being the thing that I mean, at baseline, translates your prompt into something that the video model can understand. You have two choices here, uh either LTX API, which we\'re going to talk about in 1 second, or the local encoder. Now, if you choose'

[03:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to go with the local encoder, that\'s going to cost you another 25 gigs in space, uh, but you know, at the same time, you truly have a local model. Uh, that said, I I chose not to uh, and just went with the LTX API. For that, um, all'

[04:05] [scene:talk]
